<body>
    <h1>Churn Prevention Framework</h1>

    <h2>1. Data Preparation & Feature Engineering</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Data Collection & Cleaning:</span> Gathered historical service usage, purchase transactions, and loyalty plan details from Snowflake tables. Created a new dataframe with anchor dates, replaced infinite values with <code>NaN</code>, and imputed missing entries using medians (numeric) or modes (categorical).
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Feature Creation:</span> Engineered key behavioral signals, including recency of visits, time-windowed spend (3M/6M/12M), and service-delay ratios to capture churn risk indicators.
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Scaling & Transformation:</span> Applied custom feature weighting and normalized inputs for machine learning using <code>MinMaxScaler</code>.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Model Training & Scoring</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Train/Validation/Test Split:</span> Stratified splits preserved a natural churn rate across datasets.
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Algorithm Selection & Optimization:</span> Evaluated and tuned ML frameworks like Random Forest and Gradient Boosting to optimize recall for the minority churn class.
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Scoring Pipeline:</span> Automated workflows processed data, applied transformations, and output churn risk scores, capturing ~80% of non-returning customers within 90 days.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Behavioral Segmentation & Targeting</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Clustering:</span> Used K-Means with elbow and silhouette methods to segment high-risk customers based on behavior patterns.
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Segment-Specific Campaigns:</span> Developed tailored marketing strategies for each segment to maximize engagement.
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Control Groups:</span> Held out 10% of customers in each cluster to measure the effectiveness of targeted interventions.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Measurement & Business Impact</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">A/B Testing & Statistical Significance:</span> Compared test vs. control performance to validate promotional strategies.
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Iterative Feedback Loop:</span> Insights from outcomes informed model updates, feature refinements, and new hypotheses.
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">ROI & Retention Gains:</span> Reduced churn increased customer lifetime value and optimized marketing resources.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="center">
        <hr>
    </div>

    <h2>Bottom Line</h2>
    <p>
        By leveraging data engineering, robust modeling, strategic clustering, and controlled experimentation, this framework provides actionable insights for targeted campaigns and measurable improvements in retention, ultimately driving material EBITDA growth.
    </p>
</body>

